  <div class="views-row views-row-4 views-row-even">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/china&#32;air&#32;pollution&#32;2.jpg" alt="" title="" width="180" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../clean-air-cool-climate-solving-these-problems-together">Clean Air, Cool Climate: Solving these problems together</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Jonathan Moch</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">November 15, 2016</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>Given the health risks posed by air pollution, it is easy to understand why the Chinese government wants to address this problem. However, the dilemma is that some steps to clean up air pollution can actually contribute to global warming.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../clean-air-cool-climate-solving-these-problems-together">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/measurement-and-compliance">Measurement and Compliance</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/policy-and-governance">Policy and Governance</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/united-states-china-cooperation">United States-China Cooperation</a></span>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-5 views-row-odd">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/China&#32;smog.jpg" alt="" title="" width="181" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../china‚%2580%2599s-air-pollution-standards-will-drive-technology-innovation">China‚Äôs Air Pollution Standards Will Drive Technology Innovation</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Deborah Seligsohn</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">November 04, 2016</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>While Chinese air pollution has become world famous, over the last couple of years there has been a slowly growing awareness that the Chinese government is working hard to reduce it, and in fact in the last five years pollution levels <a href="http://www.greenpeace.org/eastasia/Global/eastasia/publications/reports/climate-energy/2016/Clean%20Air%20Action%20Plan,%20The%20way%20forward.pdf">have been falling</a>. What has not yet come to world attention, and in fact, few Chinese have really focused on, is that China has the potential to become the world leader in standard setting, at least in the two most polluting sectors, power and oil and gas. What this means is that China is now or soon will be demanding new technologies and new solutions to reduce air pollution, and thus its regulatory demands will become a driver of innovation.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../china‚%2580%2599s-air-pollution-standards-will-drive-technology-innovation">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/measurement-and-compliance">Measurement and Compliance</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/policy-and-governance">Policy and Governance</a></span>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-6 views-row-even">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Obama&#32;Xi&#32;2_0.jpg" alt="" title="" width="200" height="113" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../ahead-g20-hangzhou-us-and-china-join-paris-agreement">Ahead of G20 in Hangzhou, U.S. and China Join Paris Agreement</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Chris Henderson</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">September 03, 2016</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>On September 3rd, 2016, the United States and China <a href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2016/09/03/fact-sheet-us-china-cooperation-climate-change">formally joined</a> the Paris Agreement on climate change. The announcement came at a bilateral meeting between President Barack Obama and President Xi Jinping on Saturday, ahead of the upcoming G20 summit in Hangzhou, China. The announcement provides a major boost in the momentum behind the effort needed for the Paris Agreement to enter into force, which is likely to happen before the end of 2016. In order for the agreement to enter into force, a total of 55 countries representing 55% of global GHG emissions must join. China and the United States are the world‚Äôs two largest emitters of greenhouse gases, accounting for a combined 38% of global emissions.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../ahead-g20-hangzhou-us-and-china-join-paris-agreement">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/united-states-china-cooperation">United States-China Cooperation</a></span>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-7 views-row-odd">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Obama&#32;Xi&#32;meeting_0.jpg" alt="" title="" width="200" height="118" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../chinas-climate-leadership-and-g20-summit">China&#039;s Climate Leadership and the G20 Summit</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Joanna Lewis</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">August 26, 2016</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>Climate change is the area in which China has shown perhaps the strongest international leadership. As China hosts the G20, we can expect energy and climate to be front and center.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../chinas-climate-leadership-and-g20-summit">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/united-states-china-cooperation">United States-China Cooperation</a></span>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-8 views-row-even">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/chinafaqs-renewables2.jpg" alt="" title="" width="200" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../making-chinas-economic-transition-work-global-climate-and-local-environment">Making China&#039;s Economic Transition Work for Global Climate and the Local Environment</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Valerie Karplus and Michael Davidson</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">August 24, 2016</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>When it was first announced in late 2014, China‚Äôs climate pledge was a bold and unprecedented step that gave new confidence to global efforts to mitigate climate change. This pledge, enshrined in the 2015 Paris Climate Agreement, commits the country to peak its emissions at latest by 2030 through steady reductions in carbon intensity and deployment of non-fossil energy. As the world‚Äôs largest energy user and emitter, and second largest economy, China‚Äôs move placed a significant dent in global emissions projections at the time.</p>

<p>Today, the combination of China‚Äôs economic slowdown and proactive government realignment of internal priorities toward more sustainable growth has led to lower projections of the country‚Äôs emissions trajectory. The question is no longer whether or not China will be able to meet its pledge‚Äîindeed, a peak sooner than 2030 looks well within reach, suggesting China‚Äôs climate pledge was both prudent and credible.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../making-chinas-economic-transition-work-global-climate-and-local-environment">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/renewables-and-alternative-energy">Renewables and Alternative Energy</a></span>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-9 views-row-odd">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/Yangzhou.JPG" alt="" title="" width="160" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../decline-chinas-coal-consumption-explained">Decline in China&#039;s Coal Consumption Explained</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Chris Henderson</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">July 22, 2016</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>In a post discussing the decline in China‚Äôs coal consumption, Fergus Green, London School of Economics, highlights the connection between the slowdown in energy demand growth and the change in China‚Äôs economic growth model from energy-intensive industries to high-tech manufacturing and services. Government policy is supporting non-fossil energy and limits on coal due to drivers such as climate change, energy security, air pollution, and pursuit of commercial opportunities.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../decline-chinas-coal-consumption-explained">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/coal-electricity">Coal for Electricity</a></span>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-10 views-row-even views-row-last">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/China&#32;biking.jpg" alt="" title="" width="160" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../4-lessons-scaling-sustainable-transport-us-and-chinese-cities">4 Lessons on Scaling Up Sustainable Transport in US and Chinese Cities</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Lulu Xue</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">June 16, 2016</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p><i>This post <a href="http://www.wri.org/blog/2016/06/4-lessons-scaling-sustainable-transport-us-and-chinese-cities">originally appeared</a> on WRI&rsquo;s insights blog.</i></p>

<p>Transportation is already a major source of CO2 emissions in both <a href="http://www.eia.gov/environment/emissions/carbon" />China and the United States‚Äîat 20 percent and 30 percent, respectively</a>. The percentage of people traveling by car is increasing in Chinese cities, rising from 15 percent to 34 percent in Beijing between 2002 and 2013, creating air pollution and fueling climate change.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../4-lessons-scaling-sustainable-transport-us-and-chinese-cities">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
